The President of the United States met with 24 human rights activists who were attending a Human Rights Summit organized by two U.S. nongovernmental organizations, Freedom House and Human Rights First. The meeting, hosted by National Security Advisor General James Jones, covered various issues and countries and focused on the challenges faced by human rights defenders worldwide. The President praised the activists for their work and expressed his commitment to upholding universal standards and engaging with civil society. He also emphasized the importance of recognizing the connection between development and human rights.